Rdxplorer 2 is made up of the following steps:

Step 1. Original Rdxplorer
perl Rdxplorer2.pl -Depth In=/fisher/pcsham/WO216/LP6005162-DNA_B01/Assembly/genome/bam/LP6005162-DNA_B01.bam Out=/home/zengshuai/Pairend_validator/Data/LP6005162-DNA_B01.rdxp

Step 2. Get the paired end infos
perl Rdxplorer2.pl -PairCollect In=/fisher/pcsham/WO216/LP6005162-DNA_B01/Assembly/genome/bam/LP6005162-DNA_B01.bam Out=/home/zengshuai/Pairend_validator/Data/LP6005162-DNA_B01.rdxp

Step 3. Integrate the paired ends into RD
perl Rdxplorer2.pl -PairValid In=/fisher/pcsham/WO216/LP6005162-DNA_B01/Assembly/genome/bam/LP6005162-DNA_B01.bam Out=/home/zengshuai/Pairend_validator/Data/LP6005162-DNA_B01.rdxp

############################

Instead of running Rdxplorer2 step by step, user can run the whole pipeline using a simple command:
perl Rdxplorer2.pl -All In=/fisher/pcsham/WO216/LP6005162-DNA_B01/Assembly/genome/bam/LP6005162-DNA_B01.bam Out=/home/zengshuai/Pairend_validator/Data/LP6005162-DNA_B01.rdxp
